Class GPSRectangle

  • java.lang.Object
    • wifindus.GPSRectangle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GPSRectangle
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    An immutable, serializable packet of data describing a rectangular area bound by GPS coordinates, with the purpose of mapping those coordinates to a screen space.
    Author:
    Mark 'marzer' Gillard
    See Also:

      • GPSRectangle

        public GPSRectangle(double latStart,
            double longStart,
            double latEnd,
            double longEnd)
        Creates a new GPS rectangle using the given coordinates.
        Parameters:
        latStart - The latitude component of the top-left corner of the rectangle.
        longStart - The longitude component of the top-left corner of the rectangle.
        latEnd - The latitude component of the bottom-right corner of the rectangle.
        longEnd - The longitude component of the bottom-right corner of the rectangle.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if you provide values that don't make sense
